						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the temple called Mandi-Giḍḍaṅgi.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records a gift to god Virūpāksha[Nayiṉār] and goddess Kāḷikāḍēvī in Chandragiri. It refers to the mortgage of a piece of land called Karumā[n] kāṇi on Mārgaḻi 23rd, Viḷambi, to Kāmāṇḍai, son of Kāmi Reḍḍi a <hi rend="italic">veḷḷāḻa</hi> of Āyittaṉpaḷḷi, by Kuppaṉ Kuṉṟi, son of Karumāṇi Mā[i]rāśan of Paṉaippākkam, which mortgage is stated to have been redeemed by payment of 220 <hi rend="italic">paṇam</hi> in two instalments, one of 120 <hi rend="italic">paṇam</hi> on Kārttigai 10, Śōbhakṛit, and another of 100 <hi rend="italic">paṇam</hi> on Āvaṇ 10 Kīlaka. It also mentions Añju-jātiyār. Other details are lost as the inscription is damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
